+# GDN decode megafusion (Phase 3 MVP)
+
+AITER-style decode fusion for Qwythos GDN linear-attention layers on **gfx1151** (`RDNA3.5`).
+
+## Goal
+
+Collapse the single-token decode micro-sequence:
+
+```
+ssm_conv → silu → (view q/k/v) → [L2 norm] → gated_delta_net (K=1)
+```
+
+into **one HIP kernel launch** per layer, avoiding intermediate global writes of conv+silu q/k/v tensors.
+
+Reference (vLLM AITER): `fused_reshape_causal_conv1d_update_single_token` + `fused_rearrange_sigmoid_gated_delta_rule`.
+
+## Env flag
+
+| Variable | Default | Meaning |
+|----------|---------|---------|
+| `GGML_CUDA_GDN_DECODE_FUSED` | `0` | `1` enables graph fusion + megafused decode kernel |
+
+## Architecture
+
+### Graph fusion (`ggml-cuda.cu`)
+
+At `GGML_OP_SSM_CONV`, `ggml_cuda_try_gdn_decode_megafusion()` scans forward (skipping views/no-ops) for:
+
+1. `GGML_OP_UNARY` (`SILU`) fed by the conv node
+2. `GGML_OP_GATED_DELTA_NET` with `n_tokens==1`, `S_v==128`, `K==1`, non-KDA gate (`g.ne[0]==1`)
+3. `q/k/v` as views of the silu output (L2 must already be fused via `fuse_l2_eps`, i.e. no separate `ggml_l2_norm` nodes)
+
+When matched, the backend skips conv, silu, and GDN nodes and calls `ggml_cuda_op_gdn_decode_megafused()`.
+
+This mirrors the existing `ggml_cuda_try_gdn_cache_fusion()` pattern (GDN → state cpy), but starts at conv and covers the pre-GDN path.
+
+### Kernel (`gated_delta_net_decode_fused.cu`)
+
+Grid matches tuned serial GDN decode: `(H, n_seqs, ⌈S_v/8⌉)`, 8 warps × 64 threads on gfx1151.
+
+Per block (head `h`, seq, column tile):
+
+1. **Conv1d + SiLU** — for q/k channel rows and `v[col]`, depthwise over `d_conv=4` from `conv_input` + `conv1d.weight` (same math as `ssm_conv_f32` + `ggml_cuda_op_silu_single`)
+2. **L2 normalize** q/k in-warp when `fuse_l2_eps > 0`
+3. **One GDN step** — non-KDA, `K=1`, same recurrence as `gated_delta_net_cuda` decode path
+4. Write attn output + final state (no snapshot tail)
+
+### Model graph (unchanged)
+
+`build_delta_net_fused()` in `delta-net-base.cpp` still emits the unfused op sequence; the CUDA backend elides launches at runtime. No new `cparams` flag.
+
+## Limitations (MVP)
+
+| Item | Status |
+|------|--------|
+| `S_v == 128`, `d_conv == 4` | **Required** (Qwythos) |
+| `n_tokens == 1`, `K == 1` | **Required** (decode / MTP draft step) |
+| KDA / `g.ne[0] == S_v` | Not supported |
+| Prefill (`n_tokens > 1`) | Unchanged (chunked or serial GDN) |
+| `n_rs_seq > 0` snapshot path | Not fused (different GDN `K`) |
+| Gate/beta sigmoid + softplus | **Not fused** — still separate ops before conv |
+| Conv-state writeback (`build_conv_state` cpy) | Unchanged |
+| `num_k_heads != num_v_heads` | Supported via `iq1 = h % neqk1` channel mapping |
+| Other `S_v` / `d_conv` | Falls back to unfused conv+silu+GDN |
+
+## Build
+
+Local (gfx1151):
+
+```bash
+cd llama.cpp
+cmake --build build-rocm --target ggml-hip llama-server -j$(nproc)
+```
+
+Docker fork (port **50127**):
+
+```bash
+cd /home/ai/projects/llamacpp-qwen35-rocm
+QWEN35_ROCM_FORK_CACHEBUST=$(date +%s) docker compose build llamacpp-qwen35-rocm-fork
+docker compose up -d llamacpp-qwen35-rocm-fork
+```
+
+Enable fusion in the container:
+
+```bash
+# docker-compose.yml or runtime:
+GGML_CUDA_GDN_DECODE_FUSED=1
+```
+
+## Benchmark
+
+Use the flock-wrapped script (one GPU benchmark at a time):
+
+```bash
+# Baseline (fusion off — default)
+./scripts/profile-lock.sh -- ./scripts/bench-pp-tps.sh \
+  --url http://127.0.0.1:50127 --title gdn-megafuse-off
+
+# Megafusion on (restart container with GGML_CUDA_GDN_DECODE_FUSED=1 first)
+./scripts/profile-lock.sh -- ./scripts/bench-pp-tps.sh \
+  --url http://127.0.0.1:50127 --title gdn-megafuse-mvp
+```
+
+## Results
+
+See `var/profiles/gdn-megafuse-mvp.json` after the locked benchmark run (2026-07-12).
+
+| Config | PP tok/s | Decode tok/s | Notes |
+|--------|----------|--------------|-------|
+| Prior fork v2 (50127) | 125.3 / 176.1 | 29.6 / 25.2 | short/long prompts (`STATUS.md`) |
+| Megafusion MVP | *(see JSON)* | *(see JSON)* | `GGML_CUDA_GDN_DECODE_FUSED=1`, same model/MTP settings |
+
+Expected gain: modest decode uplift (eliminates 2 kernel waves × 36 layers); PP unchanged. Exact delta depends on MTP accept rate and memory bandwidth.
+
+## Files
+
+| File | Role |
+|------|------|
+| `ggml/src/ggml-cuda/gated_delta_net_decode_fused.cu` | Megafuse kernel + matcher |
+| `ggml/src/ggml-cuda/gated_delta_net_decode_fused.cuh` | Public API |
+| `ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu` | Fusion dispatch at `SSM_CONV` |
+| `src/models/delta-net-base.cpp` | `build_delta_net_fused()` (graph producer) |
+| `ggml/src/ggml-cuda/ggml-cuda.cu` | `ggml_cuda_try_gdn_cache_fusion()` (state cpy fusion, orthogonal) |
diff --git a/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/gated_delta_net_decode_fused.cu b/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/gated_delta_net_decode_fused.cu
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..5e7c4091
--- /dev/null
+++ b/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/gated_delta_net_decode_fused.cu
@@ -0,0 +1,348 @@
+#include "gated_delta_net_decode_fused.cuh"
+#include "gated_delta_net.cuh"
+#include "unary.cuh"
+
+#include <cmath>
+
+// MVP: Qwythos decode — conv1d (d_conv=4) + silu + q/k L2 + one GDN step, S_v=128, n_tokens=1, K=1.
+
+bool ggml_cuda_gdn_decode_fused_enabled() {
+    static int enabled = -1;
+    if (enabled < 0) {
+        const char * env = getenv("GGML_CUDA_GDN_DECODE_FUSED");
+        enabled          = (env && atoi(env) != 0) ? 1 : 0;
+    }
+    return enabled > 0;
+}
+
+static bool ggml_cuda_is_view_or_noop_local(const ggml_tensor * t) {
+    return t->op == GGML_OP_VIEW || t->op == GGML_OP_RESHAPE || t->op == GGML_OP_TRANSPOSE ||
+           t->op == GGML_OP_PERMUTE || t->op == GGML_OP_NONE;
+}
+
+static const ggml_tensor * ggml_cuda_view_root(const ggml_tensor * t) {
+    while (t != nullptr && t->op == GGML_OP_VIEW) {
+        t = t->view_src;
+    }
+    return t;
+}
+
+template<int warp_size, int rows_per_lane>
+static __device__ __forceinline__ void gdn_decode_l2_normalize(float (& shard)[rows_per_lane], const float eps) {
+    float sum = 0.0f;
+#pragma unroll
+    for (int r = 0; r < rows_per_lane; r++) {
+        sum += shard[r] * shard[r];
+    }
+    const float scale = rsqrtf(fmaxf(warp_reduce_sum<warp_size>(sum), eps * eps));
+#pragma unroll
+    for (int r = 0; r < rows_per_lane; r++) {
+        shard[r] *= scale;
+    }
+}
+
+template<int S_v, int D_CONV, int NUM_WARPS>
+__global__ void __launch_bounds__(
+        (ggml_cuda_get_physical_warp_size() < S_v ? ggml_cuda_get_physical_warp_size() : S_v) * NUM_WARPS, 1)
+gdn_decode_megafuse_cuda(
+        const float * conv_input,
+        const float * conv_weight,
+        const float * g,
+        const float * beta,
+        const float * curr_state,
+        float *       dst,
+        float *       state_out,
+        int64_t       H,
+        int64_t       n_seqs,
+        int64_t       neqk1,
+        int64_t       qkv_dim,
+        int           conv_in_stride_row,
+        int           conv_in_stride_col,
+        int           conv_in_stride_seq,
+        int           conv_w_stride_col,
+        int           sb1,
+        int           sb2,
+        int           sb3,
+        float         scale,
+        float         fuse_l2_eps) {
+    const uint32_t h_idx    = blockIdx.x;
+    const uint32_t sequence = blockIdx.y;
+    const int      lane     = threadIdx.x;
+    const int      col      = blockIdx.z * blockDim.y + threadIdx.y;
+
+    constexpr int warp_sz       = ggml_cuda_get_physical_warp_size() < S_v ? ggml_cuda_get_physical_warp_size() : S_v;
+    static_assert(S_v % warp_sz == 0, "S_v must be a multiple of warp_size");
+    constexpr int rows_per_lane = (S_v + warp_sz - 1) / warp_sz;
+
+    const int64_t iq1 = h_idx % neqk1;
+
+    const int64_t q_base = iq1 * S_v;
+    const int64_t k_base = neqk1 * S_v + iq1 * S_v;
+    const int64_t v_base = 2 * neqk1 * S_v + h_idx * S_v;
+
+    const float * x_seq = conv_input + sequence * conv_in_stride_seq;
+    const float * w     = conv_weight;
+
+    auto conv_silu_channel = [&](const int64_t channel) -> float {
+        float sumf = 0.0f;
+#pragma unroll
+        for (int j = 0; j < D_CONV; j++) {
+            const float xj = x_seq[j * conv_in_stride_row + channel * conv_in_stride_col];
+            const float wj = w[j * conv_w_stride_col + channel];
+            sumf += xj * wj;
+        }
+        return ggml_cuda_op_silu_single(sumf);
+    };
+
+    float q_reg[rows_per_lane];
+    float k_reg[rows_per_lane];
+#pragma unroll
+    for (int r = 0; r < rows_per_lane; r++) {
+        const int i = r * warp_sz + lane;
+        if (i < S_v) {
+            const int64_t qc = q_base + i;
+            const int64_t kc = k_base + i;
+            q_reg[r]           = (qc < qkv_dim) ? conv_silu_channel(qc) : 0.0f;
+            k_reg[r]           = (kc < qkv_dim) ? conv_silu_channel(kc) : 0.0f;
+        } else {
+            q_reg[r] = 0.0f;
+            k_reg[r] = 0.0f;
+        }
+    }
+
+    if (fuse_l2_eps > 0.0f) {
+        gdn_decode_l2_normalize<warp_sz, rows_per_lane>(q_reg, fuse_l2_eps);
+        gdn_decode_l2_normalize<warp_sz, rows_per_lane>(k_reg, fuse_l2_eps);
+    }
+
+    const int64_t state_in_offset  = sequence * H * S_v * S_v + h_idx * S_v * S_v;
+    const int64_t state_out_offset = (sequence * H + h_idx) * S_v * S_v;
+    curr_state += state_in_offset + col * S_v;
+    state_out  += state_out_offset;
+    dst        += (sequence * H + h_idx) * S_v + col;
+
+    float s_shard[rows_per_lane];
+    ggml_cuda_pdl_sync();
+#pragma unroll
+    for (int r = 0; r < rows_per_lane; r++) {
+        const int i = r * warp_sz + lane;
+        s_shard[r]  = curr_state[i];
+    }
+
+    const int64_t gb_offset = sequence * sb3 + h_idx * sb1;
+    const float   beta_val  = beta[gb_offset];
+    const float   g_val     = expf(g[gb_offset]);
+
+    const int64_t vc = v_base + col;
+    const float   v_col = (vc < qkv_dim) ? conv_silu_channel(vc) : 0.0f;
+
+    float kv_shard = 0.0f;
+#pragma unroll
+    for (int r = 0; r < rows_per_lane; r++) {
+        kv_shard += s_shard[r] * k_reg[r];
+    }
+    const float kv_col    = warp_reduce_sum<warp_sz>(kv_shard);
+    const float delta_col = (v_col - g_val * kv_col) * beta_val;
+
+    float attn_partial = 0.0f;
+#pragma unroll
+    for (int r = 0; r < rows_per_lane; r++) {
+        s_shard[r]    = g_val * s_shard[r] + k_reg[r] * delta_col;
+        attn_partial += s_shard[r] * q_reg[r];
+    }
+    const float attn_col = warp_reduce_sum<warp_sz>(attn_partial);
+
+    if (lane == 0) {
+        dst[0] = attn_col * scale;
+    }
+
+#pragma unroll
+    for (int r = 0; r < rows_per_lane; r++) {
+        const int i              = r * warp_sz + lane;
+        state_out[col * S_v + i] = s_shard[r];
+    }
+}
+
+static void launch_gdn_decode_megafuse(
+        const float * conv_input,
+        const float * conv_weight,
+        const float * g_d,
+        const float * b_d,
+        const float * s_d,
+        float *       dst_d,
+        float *       state_d,
+        int64_t       S_v,
+        int64_t       H,
+        int64_t       n_seqs,
+        int64_t       neqk1,
+        int64_t       qkv_dim,
+        int           d_conv,
+        int           conv_in_stride_row,
+        int           conv_in_stride_col,
+        int           conv_in_stride_seq,
+        int           conv_w_stride_col,
+        int64_t       sb1,
+        int64_t       sb2,
+        int64_t       sb3,
+        float         scale,
+        float         fuse_l2_eps,
+        cudaStream_t  stream) {
+    if (S_v != 128 || d_conv != 4) {
+        return;
+    }
+
+    const int warp_size = ggml_cuda_info().devices[ggml_cuda_get_device()].warp_size;
+    const int num_warps = 8;
+    const int block_x   = warp_size <= S_v ? warp_size : S_v;
+    dim3      grid_dims(H, n_seqs, (S_v + num_warps - 1) / num_warps);
+    dim3      block_dims(block_x, num_warps, 1);
+
+    const ggml_cuda_kernel_launch_params launch_params = ggml_cuda_kernel_launch_params(grid_dims, block_dims, 0, stream);
+
+    ggml_cuda_kernel_launch(gdn_decode_megafuse_cuda<128, 4, 8>, launch_params, conv_input, conv_weight, g_d, b_d, s_d,
+        dst_d, state_d, H, n_seqs, neqk1, qkv_dim, conv_in_stride_row, conv_in_stride_col, conv_in_stride_seq,
+        conv_w_stride_col, (int) sb1, (int) sb2, (int) sb3, scale, fuse_l2_eps);
+}
+
+int ggml_cuda_try_gdn_decode_megafusion(const ggml_cgraph * cgraph, int node_idx,
+                                        ggml_cuda_gdn_decode_megafuse_args & args) {
+    if (!ggml_cuda_gdn_decode_fused_enabled()) {
+        return 0;
+    }
+
+    const ggml_tensor * ssm = cgraph->nodes[node_idx];
+    if (ssm->op != GGML_OP_SSM_CONV || ssm->type != GGML_TYPE_F32) {
+        return 0;
+    }
+
+    const int64_t d_conv = ssm->src[1]->ne[0];
+    if (d_conv != 4) {
+        return 0;
+    }
+
+    const ggml_tensor * conv_input = ssm->src[0];
+    if (conv_input->type != GGML_TYPE_F32) {
+        return 0;
+    }
+
+    const ggml_tensor * silu     = nullptr;
+    const ggml_tensor * gdn      = nullptr;
+    int                 silu_idx = -1;
+    int                 gdn_idx  = -1;
+
+    for (int j = node_idx + 1; j < cgraph->n_nodes; ++j) {
+        const ggml_tensor * n = cgraph->nodes[j];
+        if (ggml_cuda_is_view_or_noop_local(n)) {
+            continue;
+        }
+        if (n->op == GGML_OP_UNARY && ggml_get_unary_op(n) == GGML_UNARY_OP_SILU && silu == nullptr) {
+            if (n->src[0] != ssm && n->src[0]->op != GGML_OP_SSM_CONV) {
+                return 0;
+            }
+            silu     = n;
+            silu_idx = j;
+            continue;
+        }
+        if (n->op == GGML_OP_GATED_DELTA_NET) {
+            gdn     = n;
+            gdn_idx = j;
+            break;
+        }
+        if (n->op == GGML_OP_L2_NORM) {
+            return 0;
+        }
+        if (silu != nullptr) {
+            return 0;
+        }
+    }
+
+    if (gdn == nullptr || silu == nullptr) {
+        return 0;
+    }
+
+    const ggml_tensor * src_v = gdn->src[2];
+    const int64_t       S_v   = src_v->ne[0];
+    const int64_t       H     = src_v->ne[1];
+    const int64_t       n_tok = src_v->ne[2];
+    const int64_t       K     = ggml_get_op_params_i32(gdn, 0);
+
+    if (S_v != 128 || n_tok != 1 || K != 1 || gdn->type != GGML_TYPE_F32) {
+        return 0;
+    }
+
+    const ggml_tensor * src_g = gdn->src[3];
+    if (src_g->ne[0] != 1) {
+        return 0;
+    }
+
+    const ggml_tensor * silu_root = ggml_cuda_view_root(silu);
+    for (int s = 0; s < 3; ++s) {
+        const ggml_tensor * src = gdn->src[s];
+        if (src->op != GGML_OP_VIEW) {
+            return 0;
+        }
+        if (ggml_cuda_view_root(src) != silu_root) {
+            return 0;
+        }
+    }
+
+    const int64_t n_t_conv = silu->ne[1];
+    if (n_t_conv != 1) {
+        return 0;
+    }
+
+    GGML_UNUSED(H);
+    GGML_UNUSED(silu_idx);
+
+    args.ssm_conv      = ssm;
+    args.silu          = silu;
+    args.gdn           = gdn;
+    args.gdn_node_idx  = gdn_idx;
+    return gdn_idx - node_idx;
+}
+
+void ggml_cuda_op_gdn_decode_megafused(ggml_backend_cuda_context & ctx,
+                                       const ggml_cuda_gdn_decode_megafuse_args & args) {
+    const ggml_tensor * ssm = args.ssm_conv;
+    const ggml_tensor * gdn = args.gdn;
+
+    ggml_tensor * src_q     = gdn->src[0];
+    ggml_tensor * src_v     = gdn->src[2];
+    ggml_tensor * src_g     = gdn->src[3];
+    ggml_tensor * src_beta  = gdn->src[4];
+    ggml_tensor * src_state = gdn->src[5];
+
+    const int64_t S_v    = src_v->ne[0];
+    const int64_t H      = src_v->ne[1];
+    const int64_t n_seqs = src_v->ne[3];
+
+    const int64_t neqk1 = src_q->ne[1];
+    const int64_t qkv_dim =
+        src_q->ne[0] * src_q->ne[1] + gdn->src[1]->ne[0] * gdn->src[1]->ne[1] + src_v->ne[0] * src_v->ne[1];
+
+    const float * conv_input  = (const float *) ssm->src[0]->data;
+    const float * conv_weight = (const float *) ssm->src[1]->data;
+    const float * g_d         = (const float *) src_g->data;
+    const float * b_d         = (const float *) src_beta->data;
+    const float * s_d         = (const float *) src_state->data;
+    float *       dst_d       = (float *) gdn->data;
+
+    const int d_conv = (int) ssm->src[1]->ne[0];
+
+    const int conv_in_stride_row = (int) (ssm->src[0]->nb[0] / sizeof(float));
+    const int conv_in_stride_col = (int) (ssm->src[0]->nb[1] / sizeof(float));
+    const int conv_in_stride_seq = (int) (ssm->src[0]->nb[2] / sizeof(float));
+    const int conv_w_stride_col  = (int) (ssm->src[1]->nb[1] / sizeof(float));
+
+    const int64_t sb1 = src_beta->nb[1] / sizeof(float);
+    const int64_t sb2 = src_beta->nb[2] / sizeof(float);
+    const int64_t sb3 = src_beta->nb[3] / sizeof(float);
+
+    const float scale      = 1.0f / sqrtf((float) S_v);
+    const float fuse_l2    = ggml_get_op_params_f32(gdn, 1);
+    float *     state_d    = dst_d + S_v * H * n_seqs;
+
+    launch_gdn_decode_megafuse(conv_input, conv_weight, g_d, b_d, s_d, dst_d, state_d, S_v, H, n_seqs, neqk1, qkv_dim,
+        d_conv, conv_in_stride_row, conv_in_stride_col, conv_in_stride_seq, conv_w_stride_col, sb1, sb2, sb3, scale,
+        fuse_l2, ctx.stream());
+}
diff --git a/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/gated_delta_net_decode_fused.cuh b/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/gated_delta_net_decode_fused.cuh
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..bd346a09
